    <header>
        <h1>Seed Dispersal Adventure!</h1>
        <p>How Do Seeds Travel to Grow New Plants?</p>
        <div style="margin-top: 15px; font-size: 2rem;">
            <i class="fas fa-seedling"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-wind"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-water"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-dove"></i>
        </div>
    </header>
    
    <div class="intro">
        <p>Seeds need to move away from the parent plant to find space, sunlight, and soil to grow. This trip is called <strong>Seed Dispersal</strong>!</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>4 Main Travel Methods</h2>
    
    <div class="methods-grid">
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon">üçÉüí®</div>
            <div class="method-title">Wind</div>
            <p>Seeds are light and have wings or parachutes to fly.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Dandelion, Maple tree</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon">üíßüåä</div>
            <div class="method-title">Water</div>
            <p>Seeds can float on rivers, lakes, or oceans.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Coconut, Koa tree</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon">üêøÔ∏èüí©</div>
            <div class="method-title">Animals</div>
            <p>Seeds stick to fur or are eaten and pooped out later.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Berries, Rain tree</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="method-card">
            <div class="method-icon">üí•üì¢</div>
            <div class="method-title">Explosion</div>
            <p>Seed pods dry and POP! flinging seeds away.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> Pea plant, Violet</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Interactive Tree Explorer</h2>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 20px;">Click the buttons to learn about special trees!</p>
    
